window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>DENVER</p> <p>The Hallow Ranch was left to me, the first-born son. Before I inherited the ranch, I left to serve my country. When I came back to embrace my destiny, I was tricked.</p> <p>One night of lies and betrayal led me here. Without a brother. With a son. The Hallow Ranch is my focus. I have to ensure my son's future, whatever it takes. That includes ignoring the beautiful woman trying to take what's mine.</p> <p>VALERIE</p> <p>I have a job to do. Did I enjoy this job? No, but it pays for my mom's chemo. She's all I have left. When I was assigned to propose the pipeline's offer to the Hallow Ranch, I expected some old rancher.</p> <p>I never saw Denver Langston coming—gorgeous, rude, and stubborn. The Hallow Ranch account would cover our bills for two years, but this rancher isn't letting me have it. Saddle up, cowboy, because I'm not giving up without a fight.</p> <p>Contains mature themes.</p>"; 
